      "jsSymbol": "Agent.streamLegacy",
      "reason": "JS-only: tees a ReadableStream and attaches a processDataStream method to the Response. Swift callers receive an AsyncThrowingStream<JSONValue, Error> from `Agent.stream(_:)`, which is the idiomatic equivalent.",
      "swiftEquivalent": "Agent.stream(_:)"
    },
    {
      "jsSymbol": "Agent.processChatResponse / processChatResponse_vNext / processStreamResponseLegacy / processStreamResponse",
      "reason": "Private JS helpers implementing UI-message stitching and the in-stream tool-calls recursion for streamLegacy. Not public API.",
      "swiftEquivalent": "n/a (internal)"
    },
    {
      "jsSymbol": "Agent.stream client-side tool recursion",
      "reason": "JS tees the SSE into two branches (one to caller, one internal) to recurse on tool-calls. Swift Agent.stream yields raw MDS chunks; client-side tool execution during streaming uses approveToolCall/declineToolCall. Phase 2B may add a buffering broadcaster if a concrete consumer needs full parity.",
      "swiftEquivalent": "Agent.stream(_:) + approveToolCall/declineToolCall (or generate(_:) for full client-tools loop)"
    },
    {
      "jsSymbol": "AgentBuilder.transformWorkflowResult",
